wiki.text:
'Twinkle' may refer to one of the following.

* Twinkle, the common name for scintillation (astronomy), the variation of
  brightness of distant objects

'People':
* Twinkle (singer), a British pop singer in the 1960s
* Twinkle Khanna, an Indian movie actress
* Twinkle Bajpai, a female contestant in the reality show Sa Re Ga Ma Pa
  Challenge 2005

In 'science' and 'technology':
* Twinkle (software), Qt-based VoIP soft phone for Linux
* TWINKLE, a hypothetical integer factorization device
* Twinkle (app), a Twitter-type client for the iPhone OS by Tapulous
* PEO1, also called twinkle, a protein

In 'entertainment':

* Twinkle, one of the cousins from [[We Love Katamari]] and Me & My Katamari
* Twinkle, a character in Diana Wynne Jones's novel [[House of Many Ways]]
* Twinkle, a recurring fictional character in the British sit-com

* Twinkle, a sword carried by R. A. Salvatore's character Drizzt Do'Urden
